WEBVTT

00:03.303 --> 00:05.572
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"NECESSARY ROUGHNESS"...</i>

00:06.840 --> 00:07.574
I'M SEQUESTERING THE TEAM
IN A HOTEL ROOM SATURDAY NIGHT.

00:08.074 --> 00:09.242
CURFEW -- 10:00 P.M.

00:10.110 --> 00:11.511
THERE WON'T BE
ANY MORE SECOND CHANCES.

00:11.544 --> 00:12.379
T.K.:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

00:12.412 --> 00:14.547
TUCKING YOU IN.

00:14.581 --> 00:16.583
CARL IS OUR VICE PRESIDENT
OF ACCOUNTING,

00:16.616 --> 00:18.518
AND HE'S ALSO THE HEAD
OF OUR CHARITABLE FOUNDATION.

00:18.551 --> 00:20.353
SPECIAL AGENT JENKINS,
FBI.

00:20.387 --> 00:22.255
DANI'S SCHEDULE
IS ALL THERE,

00:22.288 --> 00:23.156
BUT THERE ARE THINGS THAT
SHE DOESN'T PUT ON THERE.

00:23.189 --> 00:24.457
WELL, WHEN YOU DO KNOW,

00:24.491 --> 00:25.291
THERE'LL BE SOMETHING
WAITING FOR YOU.

00:27.360 --> 00:29.295
I'M THE ONE
THE FBI IS LOOKING FOR.

00:29.329 --> 00:31.564
AND I DON'T SEE A WAY OUT.

00:31.598 --> 00:34.100
YOU HAVEN'T TOLD ME
EVERYTHING, HAVE YOU?

00:34.134 --> 00:35.402
CARL WEBBER --

00:35.435 --> 00:36.636
JUMPED OFF THE ROOF
OF HIS SoHo BUILDING.

00:36.670 --> 00:38.138
HE'S DEAD.

00:57.557 --> 01:00.093
HMM.

01:04.531 --> 01:06.332
[ GASPS ]

01:06.366 --> 01:09.202
OH, MY GOD. CARL?

01:09.235 --> 01:10.437
WHAT'S FOR BREAKFAST?

01:10.470 --> 01:12.472
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:12.505 --> 01:14.441
WISHING
I'D STOPPED FOR EGGS.

01:14.474 --> 01:16.343
MNH-MNH. NO, NO.

01:16.376 --> 01:18.311
YOU'RE DEAD.
YOU'RE DEAD, AREN'T YOU?

01:18.345 --> 01:19.512
I AM.

01:19.546 --> 01:21.214
THEN WHY ARE YOU HERE?

01:21.247 --> 01:22.515
YOU TELL ME.

01:22.549 --> 01:24.718
[ KETTLE WHISTLES ]

01:24.751 --> 01:26.419
[ ALARM CLOCK BLARING ]

01:26.453 --> 01:27.454
[ BLARING STOPS ]

01:32.525 --> 01:35.428
* I DON'T FEEL LIKE
DOING THIS *

01:35.462 --> 01:38.531
* I DON'T FEEL LIKE
DOING THAT *

01:38.565 --> 01:41.701
* DON'T FEEL LIKE
DOING ANYTHING *

01:41.735 --> 01:44.337
I HAVE...

01:44.371 --> 01:47.240
NEVER LOST A PATIENT
BEFORE.

01:47.273 --> 01:49.242
YOU MET WITH HIM TWICE.

01:49.275 --> 01:50.744
YOU NEED TO BE FAIR
TO YOURSELF.

01:50.777 --> 01:54.280
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS, OKAY?

01:54.314 --> 01:55.548
WHAT I DO KNOW IS THAT --

01:55.582 --> 01:57.584
YOU CAN'T EAT.
YOU CAN'T SLEEP.

01:57.617 --> 01:59.419
YOU'RE SECOND-GUESSING
IF YOU COULD HAVE DONE
SOMETHING DIFFERENTLY.

02:02.389 --> 02:04.691
NIGHTMARES, AS WELL?
MM-HMM.

02:04.724 --> 02:07.727
IT GETS BETTER WITH TIME.

02:07.761 --> 02:10.430
YOU DID
EVERYTHING YOU COULD.

02:10.463 --> 02:11.798
I KNOW. I WAS THERE.

02:11.831 --> 02:13.433
YEAH, BUT...

02:14.801 --> 02:17.437
...THERE'S MORE.

02:17.470 --> 02:20.607
DR. SANTINO,
C-MAC'S REQUESTED YOUR PRESENCE.

02:20.640 --> 02:23.209
UM, OKAY,
CAN YOU JUST GIVE US A MINUTE?

02:23.243 --> 02:25.578
HE SAID RIGHT NOW,
WHICH USUALLY MEANS YESTERDAY.

02:25.612 --> 02:27.347
ALL RIGHT, RON.

02:27.380 --> 02:29.282
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE HEARING
FROM JUSTICE.

02:29.315 --> 02:30.984
JUST KEEP ME POSTED
UP TO THE MINUTE.

02:31.017 --> 02:32.452
YEAH. THANKS.

02:34.320 --> 02:35.822
FBI's STILL TIGHT-LIPPED,

02:35.855 --> 02:38.558
BUT IT DOES LOOK LIKE CARL
WAS THE EYE OF THE V3 STORM.

02:41.461 --> 02:44.664
THE WHOLE THING
JUST SEEMS SO SURREAL.

02:44.698 --> 02:45.799
YOU THINK
YOU KNOW SOMEBODY.

02:45.832 --> 02:48.335
WELL...

02:48.368 --> 02:50.637
PEOPLE ARE COMPLICATED.

02:50.670 --> 02:53.239
I JUST WISH HE WOULD HAVE
COME TO ME BEFORE.

02:55.308 --> 02:57.344
HE DIDN'T TALK TO YOU
ABOUT ANYTHING, DID HE?

02:58.611 --> 03:00.313
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:00.347 --> 03:01.715
YOU DO KNOW THAT

03:01.748 --> 03:04.784
THE THERAPIST/PATIENT
PRIVILEGE LIVES ON

03:04.818 --> 03:06.586
EVEN THOUGH
SOMEONE DIES, RIGHT?

03:06.619 --> 03:08.755
NO. I DID NOT KNOW THAT.

03:08.788 --> 03:11.358
HUH.

03:11.391 --> 03:13.426
CONNOR, HEAD COUNSEL
FOR HarperCollins

03:13.460 --> 03:15.328
IS CALLING...AGAIN.

03:15.362 --> 03:18.231
THANK YOU. TELL THEM I --
I GOT MY BEST PERSON ON IT.

03:21.701 --> 03:25.372
YOU KNOW, UH,
WILLIAM GLASS, THE NOVELIST?

03:25.405 --> 03:28.775
YEAH. HE WROTE THAT "RUN"
SERIES, RIGHT?

03:28.808 --> 03:30.543
THAT SPOOKY THING,
"ROMEO & JULIET,"

03:30.577 --> 03:32.345
ZOMBIES, VAMPIRE THINGY?
MM-HMM.

03:32.379 --> 03:34.481
YEAH, WELL, BETWEEN
THE BOOKS AND THE MOVIES,

03:34.514 --> 03:35.715
THAT "THINGY"
IS WORTH BILLIONS.

03:35.749 --> 03:38.752
YEAH, WELL,
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

03:38.785 --> 03:40.653
THE PROBLEM IS
GLASS IS ABOUT NINE MONTHS LATE

03:40.687 --> 03:41.888
TURNING IN
THE LAST BOOK OF THE SERIES.

03:41.921 --> 03:45.725
MOVIE'S DUE OUT
SUMMER 2015.

03:45.759 --> 03:48.695
HE'S BEEN SINGING THAT
"I'LL BE DONE IN A WEEK"
TUNE FOR MONTHS.

03:48.728 --> 03:50.764
PUBLISHERS, MOVIE STUDIOS --
THEY DON'T LIKE THAT TUNE.

03:50.797 --> 03:52.866
THEY SUE WHEN THEY
HEAR THAT TUNE TOO MUCH.

03:52.899 --> 03:55.435
OH, WELL, THAT'S NOT GOOD.
NO, IT'S NOT.

03:55.468 --> 03:57.637
YOU GOT TO GO UP TO CONNECTICUT,
ALL RIGHT?

03:57.671 --> 03:59.539
TRY TO GET HIM
OUT OF HIS FUNK,

03:59.572 --> 04:00.740
GET HIM TO RELEASE WHATEVER
HE'S GOT TO THE PUBLISHER

04:00.774 --> 04:02.342
SO THIS THING
DOESN'T GET REALLY UGLY.

04:02.375 --> 04:04.377
OKAY.

04:04.411 --> 04:06.079
OKAY? YOU CAN GO NOW.

04:06.112 --> 04:07.547
OH.

04:15.422 --> 04:16.890
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]
Man: ON THE WHISTLE. READY?

04:21.361 --> 04:23.797
[ LAUGHTER ]

04:23.830 --> 04:25.532
WHAT Y'ALL WATCHING?

04:25.565 --> 04:26.900
HOMEBOY IN THE BATHTUB
WITH THAT CATFISH?

04:26.933 --> 04:28.535
OH, T.K.,
YOU DON'T WANT TO SEE THIS.

04:28.568 --> 04:31.371
YES, I -- A SEX TAPE?
YES, I DO! HOO-HOO!

04:31.404 --> 04:33.473
SHE'S LIKE A SPIDER MONKEY
ON A FLAGPOLE!

04:33.506 --> 04:34.607
[ LAUGHTER ]

04:37.677 --> 04:39.679
THAT LOOKS LIKE MY ASS.

04:39.713 --> 04:43.416
IT IS YOUR ASS,
YOU ASS.

04:43.450 --> 04:45.452
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]
SHE-K WENT VIRAL.

04:45.485 --> 04:46.720
MR. KING.

05:09.642 --> 05:11.544
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

05:13.747 --> 05:15.448
CAN I HELP YOU?

05:15.482 --> 05:18.418
HI, MR. GLASS.
I'M DR. DANI SANTINO.

05:18.451 --> 05:19.786
CONNOR McCLANE SENT ME.

05:19.819 --> 05:21.788
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

05:21.821 --> 05:25.692
[ LOCK CLICKS ]
OH. UM...

05:25.725 --> 05:27.894
HEY, Y-YOU KNOW, YOU GOT
A-A LOT OF PACKAGES OUT HERE.

05:27.927 --> 05:29.796
I'LL GET TO THEM LATER.

05:29.829 --> 05:35.435
MR. GLASS,
CONNOR IS WORRIED ABOUT YOU,

05:35.468 --> 05:37.470
SO HE SENT ME HERE
TO SEE IF YOU'RE OKAY.

05:37.504 --> 05:40.006
I'M FINE. I'M JUST
UNDER DEADLINE PRESSURE.

05:40.040 --> 05:42.542
I'D LIKE TO TAKE
YOUR WORD FOR THAT.

05:42.575 --> 05:43.543
UM, I WOULD.

05:43.576 --> 05:44.944
BUT I ACTUALLY --

05:44.978 --> 05:47.781
I CAN'T LEAVE HERE
UNLESS I HAVE

05:47.814 --> 05:51.451
SOME KIND OF EVIDENCE
THAT YOU'RE WELL.

05:51.484 --> 05:54.454
WHAT DO YOU WANT,
A-A PICTURE OR SOMETHING?

05:54.487 --> 05:57.657
YES. A-A PHOTO --
A PICTURE WOULD BE AWESOME.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.526
OKAY, ONE PHOTO
AND THEN YOU'LL GO?

05:59.559 --> 06:01.795
THEN I WILL GO.

06:01.828 --> 06:04.931
[ LOCKS CLICKING ]

06:04.964 --> 06:07.600
[ DOOR HINGES CREAK ]

06:07.634 --> 06:09.869
I TOLD YOU I'M FINE.

06:17.477 --> 06:18.745
COACH, I SWEAR TO YOU,
I DID NOT RELEASE THAT TAPE.

06:18.778 --> 06:20.513
I DON'T KNOW WHO DID IT,

06:20.547 --> 06:21.748
BUT I AM RACKING MY BRAIN
TRYING TO FIGURE IT OUT.

06:21.781 --> 06:23.683
I AM -- I'M VERY SOR--
MR. KING.

06:23.717 --> 06:25.919
I DON'T CARE WHO YOU SCREW
ON YOUR OWN TIME,

06:25.952 --> 06:28.788
BUT THAT TAPE WAS MADE
ON<i>MY</i>TIME.

06:28.822 --> 06:30.790
WHAT?
THAT SEXCAPADE
WAS MADE IN YOUR HOTEL ROOM

06:30.824 --> 06:33.026
BEFORE THE DETROIT GAME,

06:33.059 --> 06:35.929
WHEN YOU WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE ALONE, CORRECT?

06:35.962 --> 06:37.797
YES, SIR, BUT --

06:37.831 --> 06:40.800
SO MY CURFEW WAS VIOLATED,
MR. KING, WASN'T IT?

06:40.834 --> 06:43.870
THAT DEPENDS ON
HOW ONE INTERPRETS

06:43.903 --> 06:46.072
THE MEANING OF THE WORD
"CURFEW."

06:46.106 --> 06:48.608
NO, IT DEPENDS ON
HOW<i>I</i>INTERPRET IT.

06:48.641 --> 06:50.543
GO CLEAN OUT YOUR LOCKER.

06:50.577 --> 06:52.645
[ LAUGHS ]
COACH, CAN WE TALK ABOUT THIS?

06:52.679 --> 06:54.014
I TOLD YOU
THERE'D BE NO SECOND CHANCES.

06:54.047 --> 06:55.715
I'M A MAN OF MY WORD.

06:55.749 --> 06:57.050
SAY GOODBYE TO THE HAWKS,
MR. KING.

06:57.083 --> 06:59.452
I'M TRADING YOUR ASS.

07:01.988 --> 07:06.493
* BABY, WORK YOUR MAGIC ON ME

07:21.041 --> 07:22.642
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY, YOU'VE HAD YOUR WATER.

07:22.676 --> 07:24.077
YOU'VE USED THE RESTROOM.

07:24.110 --> 07:26.046
NOW YOU HAVE YOUR PICTURE,
DR. SANTINO.

07:26.079 --> 07:30.083
YOU CAN SHOW
AND TELL CONNOR I'M FINE.

07:30.116 --> 07:32.285
NOW, IF YOU DON'T MIND,
I HAVE TO GET BACK TO MY WORK.

07:32.318 --> 07:33.920
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

07:37.223 --> 07:39.592
[ DOOR OPENS ]

07:39.626 --> 07:40.927
Felipe:
GROCERIES, MR. GLASS.

07:40.960 --> 07:41.695
William:
UH, THANK YOU, FELIPE.

07:41.728 --> 07:43.997
I'LL PUT IT
ON YOUR TAB, SIR.

07:44.030 --> 07:45.131
THANKS A LOT.

07:47.734 --> 07:49.269
SO...

07:49.302 --> 07:52.138
YOU GET YOUR GROCERIES
DELIVERED?

07:52.172 --> 07:54.240
YEAH. UH, IT HELPS
SAVE TIME FOR MY WORK.

07:54.274 --> 07:57.243
SPEAKING OF WHICH,
I DO HAVE A DEADLINE.

07:57.277 --> 07:59.045
YOU<i>HAD</i>A DEADLINE.

07:59.079 --> 08:02.182
I'M TOLD THAT
THAT PASSED NINE MONTHS AGO.

08:02.215 --> 08:05.952
I DON'T CHOOSE WHEN TO
FIND INSPIRATION, DR. SANTINO.

08:05.985 --> 08:07.654
IT CHOOSES WHEN TO
FIND ME.

08:07.687 --> 08:11.725
AN ARTIST IS AT THE MERCY
OF CREATIVE INSTINCTS,

08:11.758 --> 08:14.227
INTANGIBLES
THAT THE LAWYERS AND AGENTS

08:14.260 --> 08:17.163
WILL NEVER UNDERSTAND.
OKAY.

08:17.197 --> 08:21.034
YOU SAY YOU'RE FINE,
BUT YOU DON'T SEEM FINE.

08:21.067 --> 08:23.203
HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN

08:23.236 --> 08:27.007
SINCE YOU'VE ACTUALLY
LEFT YOUR HOUSE?

08:31.945 --> 08:35.315
NINE MONTHS.

08:35.348 --> 08:37.717
NINE LONG MONTHS.

08:40.220 --> 08:42.956
A-AND, DR. SANTINO...
MM-HMM?

08:42.989 --> 08:46.559
...I HAVEN'T WRITTEN
A SINGLE WORD.

08:54.701 --> 08:57.337
HE IS TRADING ME
TO BUFFALO.

08:57.370 --> 08:59.639
I UNDERSTAND.
THE WEATHER'S LIKE SIBERIA.

08:59.673 --> 09:01.775
THE TEAM IS EVEN COLDER.
IT'S LAST PLACE IN THE LEAGUE.

09:01.808 --> 09:05.011
AND THE WOMEN? A BUFFALO 10
IS LIKE A MANHATTAN 3.

09:05.045 --> 09:07.347
A BUFFALO 10
IS LIKE A BUFFALO.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

09:07.380 --> 09:10.216
NOT THAT I WAS WORRIED ABOUT
HOW BUFFALO WOMEN LOOK.

09:10.250 --> 09:12.252
T.K., LISTEN.
YOU KNOW WHAT I DO FOR A LIVING?

09:12.285 --> 09:14.220
I PUT OUT FIRES.
AND I'M THE BEST THERE IS.

09:14.254 --> 09:16.122
OKAY? SO LET ME JUST
TAKE CARE OF THIS.

09:16.156 --> 09:18.258
THIS IS A TOWERING INFERNO.
YOU MIGHT NEED A BIGGER HOSE.

09:18.291 --> 09:20.393
COACH WIZ AND I
GO BACK A LONG WAY.

09:20.427 --> 09:21.828
I'M GONNA GO VISIT HIM,
AND I'M GONNA GET THIS
THING FIXED MAN-TO-MAN.

09:21.861 --> 09:23.663
THE TRADE DEADLINE
IS NEXT WEEK,

09:23.697 --> 09:25.231
SO HURRY UP BEFORE
MY CAREER GETS HYPOTHERMIA.

09:25.265 --> 09:26.633
TRUST ME, I GOT THIS.

09:26.666 --> 09:27.400
Sheera: WAIT.

09:27.434 --> 09:29.269
WHAT ABOUT THE SEX TAPE?

09:29.302 --> 09:31.004
THE BEST ACTION
IS INACTION.

09:31.037 --> 09:33.106
WHAT?! I WANT JUSTICE.
HEY, HONEY, COME ON.

09:33.139 --> 09:35.141
LOOK, CELEBRITY PHONES
GET HACKED ALL THE TIME.

09:35.175 --> 09:36.743
DON'T PUT ANYTHING
ON YOUR PHONE

09:36.776 --> 09:38.411
THAT YOU DON'T WANT
TO END UP IN THE TABLOIDS.

09:38.445 --> 09:40.213
NO MORE SEX TAPES.

09:40.246 --> 09:43.316
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I HAVE A TRADE TO KILL.

09:44.684 --> 09:46.152
IMPRESSED?

09:46.186 --> 09:47.721
I'M JUST SAYING,
YOU DON'T SEEM LIKE

09:47.754 --> 09:49.055
THE KIND OF GIRL
THAT WOULD DRINK RED EYES.

09:49.089 --> 09:50.724
THAT'S SOME STRONG STUFF.

09:50.757 --> 09:53.026
WELL, SOMEONE
KEPT ME UP ALL NIGHT.

09:53.059 --> 09:55.395
I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.
I WASN'T COMPLAINING.

09:55.428 --> 09:57.831
IN THAT CASE,
HOW ABOUT...

09:57.864 --> 10:00.100
WE LOSE SOME MORE SLEEP
THIS WEEKEND?

10:00.133 --> 10:01.801
UH, MY MOM'S
IN TOWN THIS WEEKEND,

10:01.835 --> 10:03.203
BUT SHE REALLY
WANTS TO MEET YOU.

10:04.871 --> 10:07.707
I'M KIDDING.
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:07.741 --> 10:10.043
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT THEY
SAY. THERE'S A LITTLE
TRUTH IN EVERY JOKE.

10:10.076 --> 10:11.111
WELL, NOT THAT ONE. RELAX.

10:11.144 --> 10:12.312
GOOD.

10:12.345 --> 10:14.114
I SHOULD
GET BACK TO MY DESK.

10:14.147 --> 10:15.415
DANI'S SCHEDULE'S
JAMMED TODAY.

10:15.448 --> 10:17.417
SPEAKING OF DANI,
UH...

10:17.450 --> 10:19.052
THE MAIL ROOM SAID THAT
SHE RECEIVED A PACKAGE

10:19.085 --> 10:20.353
THE NIGHT CARL DIED.

10:20.387 --> 10:22.856
YES, BUT I DON'T KNOW
WHO SENT IT.

10:22.889 --> 10:24.357
WELL,
IT'S TIME TO FIND OUT.

10:24.391 --> 10:27.794
AGENT'S MOTTO --
DO WHATEVER IT TAKES.

10:30.130 --> 10:32.298
William: LOOK AROUND.

10:32.332 --> 10:34.200
A ROOM
FILLED WITH HORROR...

10:36.069 --> 10:37.303
...THE STUFF OF NIGHTMARES.

10:37.337 --> 10:39.406
BUT WHAT SCARES ME
THE MOST?

10:41.207 --> 10:43.176
THE BLANK PAGE.

10:43.209 --> 10:46.746
I START EVERY DAY
WITH IDEAS,

10:46.780 --> 10:49.115
BUT WHEN I LOOK AT THEM
ON PAPER, THEY'RE TERRIBLE.

10:49.149 --> 10:50.483
NEXT THING I KNOW,

10:50.517 --> 10:52.719
THE DAY IS GONE,
I GOT NOTHING.

10:52.752 --> 10:56.122
AND IT'S JUST YOU
HERE IN THIS HOUSE?

10:56.156 --> 10:58.358
LET'S FACE IT,

10:58.391 --> 11:02.462
WOMEN AREN'T GONNA WANT TO
PLAY MISTRESS TO ALL THIS.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.331
WRITING'S ALWAYS BEEN
MY FIRST LOVE.

11:05.365 --> 11:08.201
I'VE BEEN DESCRIBED AS
A WORKAHOLIC

11:08.234 --> 11:09.836
IN THE BEST OF TIMES.

11:09.869 --> 11:12.372
AND IN THE WORST OF TIMES,
IT APPEARS,

11:12.405 --> 11:15.342
AGORAPHOBIC.

11:15.375 --> 11:19.379
HAVE YOU EVER SHUT YOURSELF IN
LIKE THIS BEFORE?

11:19.412 --> 11:21.414
WHEN I'M ON DEADLINE,

11:21.448 --> 11:24.484
I ALWAYS SEQUESTER
TO AVOID DISTRACTIONS.

11:24.517 --> 11:26.186
THIS TIME, THOUGH,

11:26.219 --> 11:28.355
DAYS TURN TO WEEKS
TURN TO MONTHS.

11:28.388 --> 11:31.391
I JUST DON'T WANT
TO LEAVE THE HOUSE

11:31.424 --> 11:34.361
IN CASE
I GET THE URGE TO WRITE.

11:34.394 --> 11:37.230
WELL, WILLIAM...

11:39.399 --> 11:41.868
...IT'S BEEN NINE MONTHS,

11:41.901 --> 11:44.471
SO I THINK
WE CAN BOTH AGREE

11:44.504 --> 11:47.207
THAT THIS APPROACH
IS NOT WORKING FOR YOU.

11:48.575 --> 11:53.246
IT'S TIME FOR YOU
TO LEAVE THIS HOUSE.

11:54.981 --> 11:56.516
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

11:56.549 --> 11:59.386
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S IT!
PACK IT UP!

11:59.419 --> 12:01.354
THERE HE IS. GREATNESS.

12:01.388 --> 12:03.390
FOUR-TIME LEAGUE CHAMP.

12:03.423 --> 12:05.258
THE COACH WIZ.

12:05.291 --> 12:07.994
McCLANE.
THEY LET ANYONE IN HERE.

12:08.028 --> 12:09.462
WELL,
I THREW YOUR SECURITY GUARDS

12:09.496 --> 12:10.530
A COUPLE OF
ONE DIRECTION TICKETS.

12:10.563 --> 12:11.865
BIG FANS.

12:11.898 --> 12:14.868
AND FOR YOU, LAGAVULIN.

12:14.901 --> 12:17.437
YOUR FAVORITE, RIGHT?
YEAH.

12:17.470 --> 12:18.972
YOU TELL MR. KING
TO PACK GOOD AND WARM.

12:21.341 --> 12:24.377
LISTEN, ABOUT BUFFALO.

12:24.411 --> 12:26.346
I KNOW YOU AND T.K.
HAD A ROUGH SEASON,

12:26.379 --> 12:28.281
BUT I COULD MAKE THIS
A WIN-WIN, ALL RIGHT?

12:28.314 --> 12:29.816
KILL THE TRADE.

12:29.849 --> 12:31.818
CUT T.K.
SO HE CAN BE A FREE AGENT.

12:31.851 --> 12:33.586
WHY WOULD I DO THAT
AND GET NOTHING FOR MY TROUBLE?

12:33.620 --> 12:35.889
CLEAR A BUNCH OF SPACE
UNDER THE SALARY CAP.

12:35.922 --> 12:37.023
THAT WAY YOU CAN GET YOURSELF
A SHINY NEW PLAYER

12:37.057 --> 12:38.391
BEFORE THE TRADE DEADLINE.

12:38.425 --> 12:40.226
I'M NOT UP AGAINST A CAP.

12:40.260 --> 12:42.262
BUT, MORE IMPORTANT,
MR. KING BROKE MY RULES.

12:42.295 --> 12:44.264
I WILL NOT REWARD
THAT KIND OF BEHAVIOR.

12:44.297 --> 12:45.899
IT WOULD SEND THE WRONG MESSAGE
TO THIS TEAM.

12:45.932 --> 12:47.400
RIGHT, YOU KNOW...

12:47.434 --> 12:49.469
REX'S CONTRACT IS UP
AT THE END OF THE SEASON.

12:51.938 --> 12:54.441
NEGOTIATIONS
COULD GO EASY OR...

12:54.474 --> 12:56.242
COULD BE A NIGHTMARE.

12:56.276 --> 12:58.445
END OF THE SEASON
IS A LIFETIME AWAY.

12:58.478 --> 12:59.979
BY THEN,
I'LL HAVE THE CHAMPIONSHIP

13:00.013 --> 13:01.581
AND PICK OF THE LITTER.

13:01.614 --> 13:03.216
YOU DON'T HAVE
ANY LEVERAGE HERE, McCLANE.

13:03.249 --> 13:05.585
NOT YET, APPARENTLY.

13:05.618 --> 13:08.988
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO.
KEEP IT.

13:09.022 --> 13:10.557
YOU'RE GONNA NEED IT
WHEN I FINISH WITH YOU.

13:19.366 --> 13:21.034
LET'S JUST
REVIEW YOUR OPTIONS.

13:21.067 --> 13:22.936
NO, I HAVE NONE!
THAT'S THE PROBLEM!

13:22.969 --> 13:25.071
THERE ARE ALWAYS OPTIONS,
CARL,

13:25.105 --> 13:27.540
AND WE'RE JUST GONNA FIGURE OUT
THE BEST ONE FOR YOU.

13:31.511 --> 13:34.481
WAIT A MINUTE.
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

13:34.514 --> 13:37.450
WE'VE HAD THIS CONVERSATION
BEFORE.

13:37.484 --> 13:40.053
YES, BUT I WAS ALIVE
LAST TIME.

13:44.391 --> 13:46.059
WHY ARE WE HAVING IT
AGAIN?

13:46.092 --> 13:49.095
PROBABLY BECAUSE
YOU'RE OBSESSING

13:49.129 --> 13:51.297
ABOUT SOME DETAIL
YOU MISSED --

13:51.331 --> 13:53.400
A SIGN THAT
I WAS GONNA KILL MYSELF.

13:55.068 --> 13:58.605
YES, MAYBE
I COULD HAVE STOPPED YOU.

13:58.638 --> 14:01.408
HOW? WERE YOU GONNA LOCK
ME IN A CLOSET AND WATCH
ME FOR 24 HOURS A DAY?

14:01.441 --> 14:02.442
YEAH.

14:02.475 --> 14:04.310
NO.

14:04.344 --> 14:06.513
I DON'T KNOW.

14:06.546 --> 14:09.616
YOU HAVE A CHANCE
TO MAKE THINGS RIGHT.

14:09.649 --> 14:11.985
CARL, I AM TRYING!

14:12.018 --> 14:15.055
Y-Y-YOU'VE GIVEN ME
THIS DRIVE THAT I CAN'T READ!

14:15.088 --> 14:16.890
CARL?

14:18.391 --> 14:20.527
CARL?

14:20.560 --> 14:21.928
[ SIGHS ]

14:21.961 --> 14:23.129
DON'T SCREW IT UP.

14:23.163 --> 14:24.364
[ GASPS ] MM.

14:34.207 --> 14:35.342
[ SIGHS ]

14:35.375 --> 14:37.210
I'M BEING HAUNTED.

14:37.243 --> 14:39.412
WELL, THAT'S NOT REALLY
MY AREA OF EXPERTISE.

14:41.514 --> 14:43.483
SORRY. LITTLE LEVITY.

14:43.516 --> 14:46.353
WHAT'S HAUNTING YOU --
OR WHO?

14:46.386 --> 14:47.954
[ SIGHS ]

14:47.987 --> 14:49.122
CARL.

14:49.155 --> 14:51.291
AND...

14:51.324 --> 14:52.992
THIS.

14:56.096 --> 14:59.065
HE MESSENGERED THIS TO ME

14:59.099 --> 15:00.433
ON THE NIGHT
THAT HE KILLED HIMSELF.

15:00.467 --> 15:03.003
WHAT'S ON IT?

15:03.036 --> 15:05.572
NOTHING -- AT LEAST
NOTHING THAT I UNDERSTAND,

15:05.605 --> 15:08.274
BECAUSE IT'S ENCRYPTED.

15:08.308 --> 15:09.576
I BROUGHT IT TO THREE DIFFERENT
COMPUTER STORES,

15:09.609 --> 15:12.312
AND THEY WERE ALL STUMPED.

15:12.345 --> 15:15.415
CARL SENT ME SOMETHING
THAT HE WANTED ME TO SEE,

15:15.448 --> 15:17.283
AND I CAN'T SEE IT.

15:19.085 --> 15:20.553
I COULD HAVE IT DE-ENCRYPTED,
GET BACK TO YOU.

15:24.224 --> 15:25.358
YOU DON'T TRUST ME?

15:25.392 --> 15:29.062
CARL LEFT THIS WITH<i>ME.</i>

15:29.095 --> 15:30.597
I'M NOT TAKING ANY CHANCES.

15:30.630 --> 15:34.134
I CAN'T FAIL HIM AGAIN.

15:34.167 --> 15:35.435
SO, WHAT WOULD YOU
LIKE ME TO DO?

15:37.437 --> 15:39.539
BRING SOMEONE TO DECODE IT.

15:39.572 --> 15:41.141
I NEED TO SEE WHAT'S ON IT.

15:46.279 --> 15:48.415
Sheera:
THANKS, RACHEL. YEAH.

15:48.448 --> 15:51.418
NO, I'M TOTALLY FREE NEXT WEEK.
GO AHEAD AND SET IT UP.

15:51.451 --> 15:52.552
OKAY.

15:52.585 --> 15:53.520
OKAY, BYE.

15:53.553 --> 15:55.021
WOW.

15:55.055 --> 15:56.623
OKAY, THAT WAS V3.

15:56.656 --> 15:59.626
BRAVO CALLED, AND THEY ARE
MAKING A NEW SERIES --

15:59.659 --> 16:02.328
"BRILLIANT BOMBSHELLS."

16:02.362 --> 16:05.098
THEY WANT TO TALK TO ME
ABOUT HOSTING.

16:05.131 --> 16:06.466
THAT'S DOPE, BABE!

16:06.499 --> 16:07.567
THANKS, MAN.

16:07.600 --> 16:08.668
[ LAUGHS ]

16:08.702 --> 16:10.236
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

16:12.539 --> 16:14.474
HEY, COME ON.
BABY, STOP CHECKING YOUR PHONE.

16:14.507 --> 16:17.110
CONNOR IS HANDLING IT.

16:17.143 --> 16:19.412
HE'S GONNA CALL YOU
THE SECOND HE HAS ANY NEWS.

16:19.446 --> 16:21.281
YEAH, WELL,
THAT'S EASY FOR YOU TO SAY.

16:21.314 --> 16:22.282
YOU'RE NOT
GOING TO BUFFALO.

16:22.315 --> 16:23.550
I'M SORRY.

16:23.583 --> 16:26.152
NO, I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD BE HAPPY FOR YOU.

16:26.186 --> 16:27.454
THE FISH ARE BITING!

16:27.487 --> 16:29.489
I DON'T CARE ABOUT
THE FISH.

16:29.522 --> 16:31.458
I CARE ABOUT YOU.

16:31.491 --> 16:33.293
Man: T.K., OVER HERE!
Man #2: T.K.!

16:33.326 --> 16:34.627
WHY'D YOU
RELEASE THE SEX TAPE?

16:34.661 --> 16:36.496
I DIDN'T. IT WAS PROBABLY
ONE OF YOU VULTURES.

16:36.529 --> 16:38.198
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

16:38.231 --> 16:39.499
RUMOR HAS IT BRAVO
WANTS TO DO A REALITY SHOW.

16:39.532 --> 16:41.634
SHEERA HERE'S GONNA CASH IN
WHILE YOU SIT THE BENCH.

16:41.668 --> 16:45.205
YOU KNOW WHAT? PUT
THE CAMERA DOWN. LET'S
HAVE A REAL CONVERSATION.

16:45.238 --> 16:46.706
WHOA, WHOA!
TAKE IT EASY, TAKE IT EASY!
Sheera: T.K., NO, BABY. STOP.
WHOA, WHOA!

16:46.740 --> 16:48.341
IF HE'S GONNA TALK MESS
ABOUT THE WOMAN I LOVE --

16:48.375 --> 16:49.576
WHOA, WHOA. YOU'RE SAYING
YOU TWO ARE IN LOVE?

16:49.609 --> 16:50.677
LET ME SHOOT THE WEDDING.

16:50.710 --> 16:53.279
EXCLUSIVE ON
BABY SHE-K'S FIRST PICS.

16:53.313 --> 16:55.248
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]

16:56.116 --> 16:59.319
YOU WANTED ME TO TAKE YOU
SOMEPLACE THAT INSPIRES ME.

16:59.352 --> 17:01.287
HERE WE ARE.
MM-HMM.

17:01.321 --> 17:03.390
I DON'T KNOW HOW IT'S GONNA
HELP ME WRITE, THOUGH.

17:03.423 --> 17:06.292
WELL, THE IDEA IS TO...

17:06.326 --> 17:08.495
SHAKE AWAY THE COBWEBS,
CLEAR YOUR HEAD,

17:08.528 --> 17:10.463
AND GET YOU AROUND
SOMETHING THAT,

17:10.497 --> 17:12.632
YOU KNOW,
MAKES YOU HAPPY.

17:12.665 --> 17:16.269
SO, WHY DON'T YOU
TELL ME ABOUT THIS PLACE?

17:16.302 --> 17:18.638
I USED TO WORK IN THIS PLACE
ON WEEKENDS IN HIGH SCHOOL.

17:18.672 --> 17:21.307
IT'S A FANBOY'S PARADISE.

17:21.341 --> 17:24.144
I USED TO READ ANYTHING...

17:24.177 --> 17:26.680
AND EVERYTHING
I COULD GET MY HANDS ON.

17:26.713 --> 17:29.149
[ DOOR OPENS ]
I COULDN'T AFFORD ANYTHING,

17:29.182 --> 17:30.183
BUT IT NEVER MATTERED
TO THIS GUY.

17:31.918 --> 17:34.454
WILL GLASS!
[ LAUGHS ]

17:34.487 --> 17:36.556
BEEN A WHILE!
BEEN A LONG WHILE!

17:36.589 --> 17:37.691
WHERE YOU BEEN HIDING?

17:37.724 --> 17:39.626
OH, JUST AT HOME, WRITING.

17:39.659 --> 17:42.295
UH, FRANK,
THIS IS MY FRIEND,

17:42.328 --> 17:45.231
DR. DANI SANTINO.
HELLO, FRANK.

17:45.265 --> 17:47.167
THIS IS A VERY IMPRESSIVE PLACE
YOU HAVE.

17:47.200 --> 17:48.234
THANK YOU, THANK YOU.

17:48.268 --> 17:49.536
THIS FELLA HERE

17:49.569 --> 17:50.737
HAS PRETTY MUCH
KEPT ME IN BUSINESS

17:50.770 --> 17:52.539
SINCE HIS BOOKS TOOK OFF.

17:52.572 --> 17:54.374
SPEAKING OF WHICH, FRANK,

17:54.407 --> 17:56.309
I-I SEE YOU HAVE
THAT "HORROR HILL"

17:56.343 --> 17:57.377
IN THE CASE UP THERE.

17:57.410 --> 17:58.545
MM-HMM.

17:58.578 --> 18:00.146
I'D LIKE TO GIVE THAT
A NEW HOME.

18:00.180 --> 18:01.715
IT WOULD BE MY HONOR.

18:01.748 --> 18:03.149
Man: MR. GLASS.

18:03.183 --> 18:05.218
[ LAUGHS ] OH, MY GOD!

18:05.251 --> 18:06.619
UH, THIS IS SURREAL.

18:06.653 --> 18:08.321
I CAN'T BELIEVE
IT'S REALLY YOU.

18:08.355 --> 18:10.590
UH, WOULD YOU SIGN
AN AUTOGRAPH FOR ME?

18:10.623 --> 18:12.392
SURE.

18:12.425 --> 18:13.693
I ALWAYS
REREAD THE SERIES

18:13.727 --> 18:15.495
BEFORE THE NEXT MOVIE
COMES OUT.

18:15.528 --> 18:16.730
IT TOTALLY INSPIRES ME.

18:16.763 --> 18:18.698
WHO, UH -- WHO SHOULD I
MAKE THIS OUT TO?

18:18.732 --> 18:21.167
"TO DAVID AND ARIEL,

18:21.201 --> 18:23.570
THE REAL-LIFE
ANJELICA AND RAFAEL."

18:23.603 --> 18:24.571
OH!

18:28.408 --> 18:30.577
IS "RUN: THE FINAL SIEGE"
GONNA BE FINISHED SOON?

18:33.413 --> 18:34.781
UH, HOPEFULLY SOON, YEAH.

18:36.649 --> 18:38.785
WILLIAM, UH,
THIS CARD DECLINED.

18:38.818 --> 18:40.587
YOU'RE KIDDING.
THAT -- THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

18:40.620 --> 18:42.422
THIS IS A BLACK CARD.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

18:42.455 --> 18:43.790
LET ME GET TO
THE BOTTOM OF THIS, ALL RIGHT?

18:43.823 --> 18:45.325
I'M GONNA MAKE A PHONE CALL
RIGHT NOW.

18:45.358 --> 18:46.426
SORRY, FRANK.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
OKAY.

18:48.762 --> 18:50.764
FRANK, HOW MUCH
IS THAT COMIC BOOK?

18:50.797 --> 18:52.799
IT'S 11.
OOH!

18:52.832 --> 18:53.833
AWESOME.
NO, NO.

18:53.867 --> 18:55.702
$11,000.

18:55.735 --> 18:58.204
WHAT? FOR THAT?

18:58.238 --> 18:59.839
YES.

18:59.873 --> 19:03.777
FRANK, DO YOU --
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA, UH,

19:03.810 --> 19:06.312
WHAT THE LIMIT IS
ON THOSE BLACK CREDIT CARDS?

19:06.346 --> 19:08.615
AFRAID I DO.
$500,000.

19:08.648 --> 19:09.716
WHAT?

19:09.749 --> 19:10.517
A MONTH.

19:13.420 --> 19:14.721
CARL SENT THE PACKAGE?

19:14.754 --> 19:16.456
THAT'S WHAT
THE MESSENGER SERVICE SAID.

19:16.489 --> 19:17.791
AND IT WASN'T EASY
TO GET THE INFO.

19:17.824 --> 19:20.293
I HAD TO HAVE DRINKS WITH NED
ON THURSDAY.

19:20.326 --> 19:22.295
WHY WOULD CARL
SEND SOMETHING TO DANI?

19:22.328 --> 19:24.397
WAS HE A PATIENT?
NOT THAT I KNOW OF.

19:24.431 --> 19:26.633
I NEED YOU TO FIND OUT
WHAT WAS IN THAT PACKAGE.

19:26.666 --> 19:28.335
HOW?

19:28.368 --> 19:29.502
GET CREATIVE.

19:36.376 --> 19:38.545
Dani: YOU MAXED OUT
YOUR BLACK CARD.

19:38.578 --> 19:40.847
I CAN'T IMAGINE
THAT IT'S EASY

19:40.880 --> 19:43.750
TO SPEND THAT KIND OF MONEY
ON A MONTHLY BASIS.

19:43.783 --> 19:46.853
WELL, I'M LOOKING FOR
THINGS TO INSPIRE ME.

19:46.886 --> 19:49.456
OKAY.
WHAT KIND OF THINGS?

19:49.489 --> 19:53.326
YOU KNOW, LIKE MEMORABILIA
FROM MY MOVIES, BOOKS.

19:53.360 --> 19:54.828
THERE'S A LOT OF THAT STUFF
ON eBay, YOU KNOW.

19:54.861 --> 19:57.297
THEN THERE'S THE, UH,
ANTIQUE SWORD

19:57.330 --> 19:58.765
FROM THE MING DYNASTY.

19:58.798 --> 20:01.501
AND, UH...

20:01.534 --> 20:03.737
I DON'T KNOW.
IT JUST ADDS UP.

20:03.770 --> 20:05.805
MAYBE I'M A SHOPAHOLIC,
TOO.

20:05.839 --> 20:08.875
SHOPAHOLIC, AGORAPHOBIC --
YOU KNOW,

20:08.908 --> 20:11.578
ONE MORE THING AND
WE GOT OURSELVES
A TRIFECTA, DOC.

20:11.611 --> 20:14.681
SHOPAHOLICS SHOP
TO RELIEVE STRESS.

20:14.714 --> 20:17.650
THE THINGS THEY BUY
HAVE NO MEANING,

20:17.684 --> 20:20.387
AND THAT IS NOT
WHAT YOU ARE DESCRIBING.

20:20.420 --> 20:21.855
OKAY, SO, NO,
I DON'T THINK THAT

20:21.888 --> 20:23.590
THIS IS ABOUT
A SHOPPING ADDICTION.

20:23.623 --> 20:24.924
I THINK THIS IS ABOUT YOU

20:24.958 --> 20:27.360
DOING EVERYTHING
AND ANYTHING

20:27.394 --> 20:28.895
NOT TO WRITE.

20:28.928 --> 20:32.432
WHAT IS IT ABOUT THIS BOOK

20:32.465 --> 20:34.901
THAT IS SO DIFFERENT
FROM THE REST?

20:34.934 --> 20:35.769
WELL, IT'S THE END,
ISN'T IT?

20:39.105 --> 20:43.677
MAYBE
I DON'T WANT IT TO END.

20:43.710 --> 20:47.614
IT'S BEEN PART OF MY LIFE
FOR EIGHT YEARS.

20:47.647 --> 20:50.450
I DON'T WANT TO
DISAPPOINT THE FANS.

20:52.852 --> 20:55.655
BUT THIS...

20:55.689 --> 20:57.691
IS A LOT HARDER THAN
I THOUGHT IT WAS GONNA BE.

20:57.724 --> 21:01.861
IT'S LIKE SAYING GOODBYE
TO OLD FRIENDS.

21:05.865 --> 21:08.635
I HAVE AN IDEA.

21:08.668 --> 21:12.639
I WANT YOU TO WRITE 10 PAGES
FOR ME BY THE NEXT SESSION

21:12.672 --> 21:15.442
ABOUT ABSOLUTELY ANYTHING,

21:15.475 --> 21:17.744
EXCEPT "RUN."

21:25.752 --> 21:27.587
SO, CONNOR McCLANE.

21:27.620 --> 21:29.622
MUST HAVE A DAMN GOOD REASON
TO SHUFFLE UP TO BUFFALO.

21:29.656 --> 21:32.726
OH, IT WAS JUST A HOP, SKIP,
AND A G-5 JUMP TO GET HERE.

21:32.759 --> 21:35.862
PLUS, THE STEAKS IN BUFFALO --
THE BEST.

21:35.895 --> 21:37.597
ANY RECOMMENDATIONS?

21:37.630 --> 21:40.467
YEAH.
PORTERHOUSE, EVERY TIME.

21:40.500 --> 21:42.836
AND, UH...

21:42.869 --> 21:46.506
YOU MIGHT WANT TO STAY AWAY
FROM THE KING CRAB SPECIAL.

21:46.539 --> 21:48.508
[ SCOFFS ]
TERRENCE KING.

21:48.541 --> 21:50.377
NOT TRYING TO KEEP ME

21:50.410 --> 21:51.745
FROM GETTING MY FANCY,
NEW WIDE RECEIVER?

21:51.778 --> 21:53.480
NO, NO, NO, I JUST HAD

21:53.513 --> 21:54.848
A COUPLE OTHER CLIENTS IN MIND,
THAT'S ALL.

21:54.881 --> 21:56.883
I'M LISTENING.

21:56.916 --> 21:58.785
JORDAN FOLEY FROM DALLAS --

21:58.818 --> 22:00.720
CHEAPER,
BUT HIS STATS ARE GOING UP.

22:00.754 --> 22:03.823
DOUG RYBURN FROM SAN FRAN.

22:03.857 --> 22:05.725
ALL-STAR.
BUILD A WHOLE TEAM AROUND HIM.

22:05.759 --> 22:07.694
RYBURN IS GOOD.

22:07.727 --> 22:10.764
FOLEY'S DAMN GOOD,
BUT TERRENCE KING --

22:10.797 --> 22:11.664
THAT'S THE REAL GUY
FOR THIS TEAM.

22:13.833 --> 22:17.771
JAY, YOU BELIEVE IN SANTA,
DON'T YOU?

22:17.804 --> 22:19.773
ALL RIGHT,
PRETEND I'M SANTA, OKAY,

22:19.806 --> 22:21.541
AND YOU CAN HAVE
ANY PLAYER YOU WANT.

22:21.574 --> 22:22.776
ANYONE?
ANYONE.

22:22.809 --> 22:25.545
OKAY. ODELL STEWART.

22:25.578 --> 22:27.514
HOW ABOUT
SOMEONE SANTA REPRESENTS?

22:27.547 --> 22:29.516
THAT'S MY BOTTOM LINE.

22:29.549 --> 22:31.518
DELIVER ME ODELL STEWART,

22:31.551 --> 22:32.952
T.K. CAN UNPACK HIS BAGS.

22:32.986 --> 22:34.587
ALL RIGHT.

22:36.790 --> 22:39.426
JASMINE,
FIND OUT WHO REPS ODELL STEWART.

22:39.459 --> 22:40.593
YOU'VE GOT FIVE SECONDS.

23:00.947 --> 23:02.549
HEY.

23:02.582 --> 23:04.751
PACKING UP MY STUFF?
UH, YEAH.

23:04.784 --> 23:06.720
READY TO GO.

23:06.753 --> 23:08.655
YOU ARE ALWAYS
ONE STEP AHEAD OF ME.

23:08.688 --> 23:09.989
[ CHUCKLES ] I TRY.

23:10.023 --> 23:11.458
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT, OKAY?

23:11.491 --> 23:12.592
THANKS. YOU TOO.

23:21.001 --> 23:23.636
[ SIGHS ]

23:32.779 --> 23:34.547
IT DOESN'T HAVE TO BE TONIGHT,
BUT...

23:34.581 --> 23:36.483
Tiffany: ALL RIGHT.

23:36.516 --> 23:38.618
WHAT TIME?

23:38.651 --> 23:40.620
PALOMA.

23:40.653 --> 23:42.989
I WAS JUST SAYING GOOD NIGHT
TO TIFFANY HERE.

23:43.023 --> 23:45.125
GOOD NIGHT, TIFFANY.

23:45.158 --> 23:47.093
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING,
YOU HAVE MY NUMBER.

23:47.127 --> 23:49.095
MM-HMM.

23:49.129 --> 23:50.830
YOU'RE WORKING LATE.

23:50.864 --> 23:53.700
SO ARE YOU, APPARENTLY.

23:53.733 --> 23:56.069
LOOKS LIKE TIFFANY'S
ON THE FAST TRACK, TOO.

23:56.102 --> 23:57.771
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.

23:57.804 --> 24:00.240
YEAH, WELL,
IT LOOKS LIKE THAT.

24:00.273 --> 24:01.675
DON'T PLAY INNOCENT,
PALOMA.

24:01.708 --> 24:03.243
YOU DON'T WEAR IT WELL.

24:03.276 --> 24:06.112
YOU KNOW WHAT THE DEAL IS.

24:06.146 --> 24:08.181
YOU GIVE ME WHAT I WANT,
I GIVE YOU WHAT YOU WANT.

24:08.214 --> 24:09.649
IT'S PRETTY SIMPLE.

24:09.683 --> 24:12.118
NOW...

24:12.152 --> 24:13.620
YOU HAVE
SOMETHING FOR ME?

24:13.653 --> 24:16.589
ACTUALLY, I --
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

24:16.623 --> 24:17.323
UM...

24:20.660 --> 24:23.129
IT'S DANI.
SHE FORGOT SOMETHING.

24:23.163 --> 24:24.831
SHE'S ON HER WAY BACK.

24:24.864 --> 24:27.300
PALOMA?

24:27.334 --> 24:28.668
THE PACKAGE.

24:34.140 --> 24:35.608
Nico: ARE YOU SURE
YOU LEFT IT IN YOUR PURSE?

24:35.642 --> 24:36.876
OF COURSE I'M SURE.

24:36.910 --> 24:38.078
AND I TORE APART MY HOUSE.

24:38.111 --> 24:39.679
I TORE APART MY CAR.

24:39.713 --> 24:42.215
AND IF IT'S NOT HERE,
THEN I --

24:42.248 --> 24:43.283
IS THIS
WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR?

24:43.316 --> 24:45.618
WHERE DID YOU FIND IT?

24:45.652 --> 24:46.886
UNDER THE DESK.

24:46.920 --> 24:48.254
IT MUST HAVE
FALLEN OUT OF YOUR PURSE.

24:48.288 --> 24:51.091
OH, YOU ARE A LIFESAVER.

24:51.124 --> 24:52.092
THANK YOU, PALOMA.

24:52.125 --> 24:53.059
GOOD NIGHT.

24:53.093 --> 24:54.094
GOOD NIGHT.

24:54.127 --> 24:54.861
OY.

24:56.863 --> 24:58.264
SORRY FOR
THE FALSE ALARM.

24:58.298 --> 24:59.766
IT'S JUST THAT
I-I CAN'T SCREW THIS UP.

24:59.799 --> 25:01.634
UNDERSTOOD.

25:01.668 --> 25:03.269
SO YOU HAVE SOMEONE
THAT CAN DECODE IT?

25:03.303 --> 25:04.270
FRIDAY NIGHT, YOUR HOUSE.

25:04.304 --> 25:05.271
OKAY.

25:05.305 --> 25:08.074
UM...

25:08.108 --> 25:12.145
CAN YOU HOLD ON TO IT
TILL THEN?

25:12.178 --> 25:14.080
SURE YOU TRUST ME?

25:14.114 --> 25:16.316
NO.

25:16.349 --> 25:19.753
BUT RIGHT NOW I'M NOT SURE
I CAN TRUST MYSELF, SO...

25:22.655 --> 25:25.692
* MM-MM, MM-MM, MM-MM

25:25.725 --> 25:27.293
[ SIGHS ]

25:27.327 --> 25:29.629
* SEE, THE BOY GOT IT BAD

25:29.662 --> 25:32.832
* GOT IT REAL BAD

25:32.866 --> 25:36.102
* NOBODY NEEDS TO TELL HIM SO

25:39.706 --> 25:42.108
* HE'S BEEN WORKING ON A PLAN
FOR SO LONG NOW... *

25:42.142 --> 25:44.344
HEY.

25:44.377 --> 25:47.747
HEY.

25:47.781 --> 25:48.848
I'M SORRY.
DID I WAKE YOU?

25:48.882 --> 25:49.949
YEAH.

25:49.983 --> 25:51.885
IT'S ALL RIGHT, THOUGH.

25:51.918 --> 25:53.820
I HAVE TO GET UP ANYWAY.

25:55.722 --> 25:57.657
YOU SLEEP OKAY?
[ SIGHS ]

25:57.691 --> 26:00.160
C-MAC'S GONE AWOL,
I MEAN...

26:00.193 --> 26:02.729
IT'S DRIVING ME NUTS.

26:02.762 --> 26:04.197
[ SIGHS ]

26:04.230 --> 26:06.700
I'M A DOER, NOT A WAITER.

26:06.733 --> 26:09.936
WELL, THAT'S WHAT
I LIKE ABOUT YOU.

26:09.969 --> 26:11.371
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:11.404 --> 26:13.306
OR SHOULD I SAY LOVE?

26:13.340 --> 26:14.874
[ LAUGHS ]

26:14.908 --> 26:16.743
OH, I KNOW.
IT JUST KIND OF POPPED OUT.

26:16.776 --> 26:18.311
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

26:18.345 --> 26:19.813
TOO SOON, HUH?

26:19.846 --> 26:22.382
NOT SOON ENOUGH.

26:22.415 --> 26:25.385
SO, IT'S OFFICIAL.

26:25.418 --> 26:26.920
WE ARE IN LOVE.

26:28.722 --> 26:29.356
[ LAUGHS ]

26:32.292 --> 26:33.727
SHOULD I ISSUE
A PRESS RELEASE?

26:35.295 --> 26:36.796
NO, I'M JOKING.

26:36.830 --> 26:38.231
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
MM. SHOOT.

26:38.264 --> 26:39.399
I GOT TO GET GOING.

26:39.432 --> 26:41.935
I HAVE THREE MEETINGS TODAY
BACK TO BACK.

26:45.972 --> 26:48.375
[ WATER RUNNING ]
HATE WHEN YOU LEAVE,
BUT LOVE WATCHING YOU GO.

26:48.408 --> 26:50.677
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

26:53.413 --> 26:55.882
HEY, SORRY,
NO, THAT'S MINE.

26:55.915 --> 26:57.884
GOD, MY PHONE HAS BEEN
RINGING OFF THE HOOK.

26:57.917 --> 26:59.753
HEY, RACHEL.

26:59.786 --> 27:01.688
YEAH, WE'RE CONFIRMED.

27:01.721 --> 27:04.391
[ HUMMING ]

27:04.424 --> 27:06.893
MY ASSISTANT SAID
THIS WAS A DIRE EMERGENCY,

27:06.926 --> 27:09.829
SO SOMEONE I ACTUALLY GIVE
A CRAP ABOUT BETTER BE DYING.

27:09.863 --> 27:11.231
MY BAD -- I TOLD THEM

27:11.264 --> 27:13.266
OUR TEST RESULTS
CAME BACK POSITIVE,

27:13.299 --> 27:14.968
AND HE WANTED ME TO
SHARE THE HAPPY NEWS
WITH YOU IN PERSON.

27:15.001 --> 27:17.737
[ LAUGHS SARCASTICALLY ]
NOT THE SHARPEST KNIFE,
THAT KID.

27:17.771 --> 27:19.439
WHAT DO YOU WANT, CONNOR?

27:19.472 --> 27:21.775
[ SIGHS ]
I NEED YOUR HELP.

27:23.743 --> 27:27.280
I NEED TERRENCE KING
TO BECOME A FREE AGENT.

27:27.313 --> 27:29.482
YOU REALIZE
HE'S YOUR CLIENT.

27:29.516 --> 27:31.985
YES. AND ODELL STEWART
IS YOUR CLIENT.

27:32.018 --> 27:35.422
SO YOU WANT ODELL TO GO
TO BUFFALO INSTEAD OF T.K.

27:35.455 --> 27:36.556
WELL, THEY'RE PREPARED
TO GIVE HIM

27:36.589 --> 27:39.993
THE MULTI-YEAR DEAL YOU'RE
LOOKING FOR, A SIGNING BONUS.

27:40.026 --> 27:41.995
IT'S FASCINATING
HOW YOU MANAGE

27:42.028 --> 27:44.764
TO DO YOUR JOB AND MINE.

27:44.798 --> 27:47.334
LET ME GUESS.
YOU WANT MY COMMISSION, TOO?

27:47.367 --> 27:50.937
A SIMPLE YES
WOULD SUFFICE.

27:50.970 --> 27:53.340
WELL, YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE TO
SWEETEN THE POT.

27:53.373 --> 27:56.843
HUH. WANT ME TO STIR A LITTLE
HONEY INTO THE DEAL, HUH?

27:56.876 --> 27:58.311
THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING.

28:00.280 --> 28:02.315
HOW ABOUT I GIVE YOU...

28:02.349 --> 28:03.483
CALEB JONES?

28:03.516 --> 28:05.352
THE AGENT?

28:05.385 --> 28:06.853
HE ALREADY WORKS FOR ME.

28:10.023 --> 28:11.958
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

28:11.991 --> 28:14.361
I OFFERED HIM
DOUBLE WHAT YOU'RE PAYING.

28:14.394 --> 28:16.830
BIG AGENCY,
BIGGER PERKS.

28:16.863 --> 28:19.099
HOT SHOT LIKE HIM --
NOT GONNA BE ABLE TO SAY NO.

28:19.132 --> 28:20.367
WHEN WAS HE
PLANNING ON TELLING ME?

28:20.400 --> 28:21.768
I DON'T KNOW.

28:21.801 --> 28:23.370
ABOUT 20 MINUTES...
[ SCOFFS ]

28:23.403 --> 28:24.004
...GIVE OR TAKE.

28:31.544 --> 28:32.979
WHAT'S THIS?

28:33.013 --> 28:36.049
FORGET 10 PAGES.
THAT'S 75.

28:36.082 --> 28:39.052
THAT IS FANTASTIC!
I KNEW THAT YOU COULD --

28:39.085 --> 28:41.888
OF MY BRAND-NEW NOVEL.

28:41.921 --> 28:43.790
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOUR NEW NOVEL?

28:43.823 --> 28:45.859
MY WRITER'S BLOCK
IS CURED.

28:45.892 --> 28:47.961
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN IT, DOC.
MY FINGERS WERE FLYING.

28:47.994 --> 28:51.564
HOW DO YOU THINK YOUR PUBLISHERS
ARE GONNA REACT TO THIS?

28:51.598 --> 28:53.800
AREN'T YOU HAPPY FOR ME?

28:53.833 --> 28:55.468
I FINALLY FEEL FREE

28:55.502 --> 28:58.004
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN LIKE NINE MONTHS.

28:58.038 --> 29:00.540
THIS IS NOT FREEDOM.
THIS IS AVOIDANCE.

29:03.043 --> 29:06.112
I THOUGHT THAT
RAPHAEL AND ANJELICA

29:06.146 --> 29:08.882
WOULD BE TOGETHER FOREVER.

29:08.915 --> 29:13.019
YOU CAN WRITE
WHATEVER END YOU WANT FOR THEM.

29:13.053 --> 29:15.488
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

29:15.522 --> 29:18.024
NO END
CAN DO "RUN" JUSTICE.

29:18.058 --> 29:21.027
IF I CAN'T DO IT WELL,
I'M NOT GONNA DO IT.

29:21.061 --> 29:22.395
I'M NOT GONNA DO IT
AT ALL.

29:22.429 --> 29:24.964
TELL CONNOR
TO TELL MY PUBLISHER

29:24.998 --> 29:28.435
THAT IF THEY WANT AN END
TO THE "RUN" SERIES,

29:28.468 --> 29:32.105
THEY'VE GOT TO
WRITE IT THEMSELVES.

29:32.339 --> 29:33.473
WHAT?
I CAN'T DO IT.

29:33.506 --> 29:35.375
IT CAN'T BE DONE.

29:35.408 --> 29:37.143
OH, MY GOD.

29:40.947 --> 29:42.882
<i>ODELL STEWART</i>
<i>TRADED TO BUFFALO</i>

29:42.916 --> 29:44.918
<i>IN A MOVE</i>
<i>THAT SURPRISED INSIDERS.</i>

29:44.951 --> 29:47.554
<i>RUMORS HAD TERRENCE KING I.D.'d</i>
<i>TO MAKE THE MOVE UPSTATE.</i>

29:47.587 --> 29:50.023
YOU ARE A SON OF A BITCH,
McCLANE.

29:50.056 --> 29:52.892
HEY, COACH,
THANKS FOR STOPPING BY.

29:52.926 --> 29:54.527
YOU READY TO OPEN
THAT BOTTLE OF SCOTCH NOW?

29:54.561 --> 29:57.197
YOU MAY HAVE WON THE BATTLE,
BUT YOU LOST THE WAR.

29:57.230 --> 29:58.498
OH, YEAH?
WHY IS THAT?

29:58.531 --> 30:00.100
'CAUSE I'M NOT
CUTTING HIM.

30:00.133 --> 30:02.135
YOU GET ME
SOMETHING I WANT,

30:02.168 --> 30:05.071
OR T.K. SITS ON THE BENCH
FOR THE REST OF THE YEAR.

30:05.105 --> 30:07.173
REALLY? YOU'RE GONNA
DEACTIVATE HIM JUST TO SPITE ME?

30:07.207 --> 30:08.408
YOU'RE SERIOUS?

30:08.441 --> 30:10.543
AS A FAT KID ON HALLOWEEN.

30:13.646 --> 30:15.448
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

30:15.482 --> 30:17.450
FIRST-ROUND DRAFT PICK,
TOP 15 --

30:17.484 --> 30:20.053
ONE OF THOSE FAT BOYS I CAN
PLUG IN TO MY DEFENSIVE LINE.

30:23.390 --> 30:24.991
TRADE DEADLINE'S
IN 21 HOURS.

30:25.025 --> 30:27.027
CHOP-CHOP.

30:27.060 --> 30:30.096
ALL RIGHT. WE GOT 21 HOURS
TO MOVE A MOUNTAIN.

30:30.130 --> 30:31.965
GET AHOLD OF
PHILLY, MIAMI, AND DALLAS.

30:31.998 --> 30:33.500
YEAH.
WHO ARE YOU CALLING?

30:33.533 --> 30:35.035
GOD.

30:35.068 --> 30:36.903
WE NEED A MIRACLE.

30:59.325 --> 31:02.028
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:02.062 --> 31:04.164
<i>WILL ODELL STEWART BE THE MAN</i>

31:04.197 --> 31:06.132
<i>TO BRING BUFFALO</i>
<i>BACK TO HIS PAST GLORY?</i>

31:06.166 --> 31:08.168
OOH, HE LOVES HER.

31:08.201 --> 31:10.003
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:10.036 --> 31:10.370
OH, THAT'S JUST
ONE HEADLINE.

31:10.904 --> 31:13.273
"T.K. LOVES SHE-K."

31:13.306 --> 31:15.408
I DON'T THINK YOUR EYES
WOULD SHINE THIS BRIGHT

31:15.442 --> 31:16.943
IF I BOUGHT YOU DIAMONDS.

31:18.411 --> 31:22.582
WELL, I GUESS THERE'S
ONLY ONE WAY TO FIND OUT.

31:22.615 --> 31:25.952
<i>RUMORS ARE HIS MOST RECENT</i>
<i>OFF-FIELD ISSUES MOTIVATED...</i>

31:25.985 --> 31:27.454
HM.
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:27.487 --> 31:29.289
<i>BUT BOTH BUFFALO AND NEW YORK</i>
<i>OFFICIALS</i>

31:29.322 --> 31:30.490
<i>ARE NEGLECTING TO COMMENT.</i>

31:30.523 --> 31:32.025
[ TELEVISION BEEPS ]

31:32.058 --> 31:33.393
SHEERA,

31:33.426 --> 31:37.097
IF YOU SAY NO...

31:37.130 --> 31:38.531
I'LL NEVER
BRING THIS UP AGAIN.

31:40.400 --> 31:43.236
BUT DID YOU...

31:43.269 --> 31:45.972
LEAK THAT TAPE OF US?

31:46.006 --> 31:47.340
WHAT?!

31:47.374 --> 31:49.109
OKAY, WHOA.

31:49.142 --> 31:51.444
T.K.,
WHERE IS THIS COMING FROM?

31:53.480 --> 31:58.551
BUT, I MEAN,
ONCE IT'S OUT THERE,

31:58.585 --> 32:01.354
IT'S, YOU KNOW,
NOT LIKE I'M RUNNING FROM IT.

32:01.388 --> 32:05.291
WHOLE EMPIRES
HAVE BEEN MADE ON SEX TAPES,

32:05.325 --> 32:07.560
SO WHY HIDE FROM IT?

32:07.594 --> 32:10.096
WELL, YOU'RE
DEFINITELY NOT HIDING.

32:10.130 --> 32:12.332
BUT I DID
ASK YOU A QUESTION.

32:22.542 --> 32:25.478
[ SIGHS ] GOD.
LISTEN. NO -- NO, HEY, LISTEN.

32:25.512 --> 32:27.580
I WOULD NEVER HAVE DONE THIS,
I SWEAR,

32:27.614 --> 32:29.282
IF I THOUGHT
FOR ONE SECOND

32:29.315 --> 32:30.650
THAT IT WAS GONNA
HURT YOUR CAREER.

32:30.684 --> 32:32.585
[ SCOFFS ]
I DID IT FOR US, OKAY?

32:32.619 --> 32:34.421
I DID IT FOR SHE-K.

32:34.454 --> 32:36.623
YOU AND I --
WE ARE AN "IT" COUPLE NOW.

32:36.656 --> 32:40.293
WE'RE LIKE -- LIKE
THE NEXT KANYE AND KIM, OKAY?

32:40.326 --> 32:42.395
WE ARE DOMINATING
SOCIAL MEDIA.

32:42.429 --> 32:44.664
THIS IS A GOOD THING.
PEOPLE KNOW US NOW.

32:44.698 --> 32:47.534
PEOPLE KNOW
WHO YOU ARE NOW.

32:47.567 --> 32:49.369
THEY ALREADY KNEW WHO I WAS
FOR A LONG TIME.

32:49.402 --> 32:52.138
AND NOW THEY KNOW
A HELL OF A LOT MORE ABOUT ME

32:52.172 --> 32:53.306
THAN I WANTED THEM TO,
THANKS TO YOU.

32:55.442 --> 32:56.576
T.K.

32:56.609 --> 32:58.311
T.K., BABY, WAIT.

32:58.345 --> 32:59.679
I'M SORRY.

32:59.713 --> 33:01.281
WAIT, STOP.
CAN WE JUST --

33:01.314 --> 33:02.549
CAN WE
TALK ABOUT THIS TOMORROW?

33:02.582 --> 33:05.218
THERE'S NOTHING
TO TALK ABOUT.

33:14.294 --> 33:15.595
ALL RIGHT,
LET ME LAY THIS OUT FOR YOU.

33:15.628 --> 33:17.430
I'D LIKE YOU TO PART WITH NORRIS
FOR A DRAFT PICK.

33:17.464 --> 33:19.599
JERRY, IT'S A WIN-WIN SITUATION.

33:21.468 --> 33:22.135
KEEP THEM COMING.

33:22.168 --> 33:24.571
ALL RIGHT, JERRY, WE GOT A DEAL?

33:24.604 --> 33:26.272
LOOK, PAULIE,
YOU'RE A BEAUTIFUL MAN,

33:26.306 --> 33:27.707
BUT THIS IS AN UGLY DEAL.

33:27.741 --> 33:29.175
YEAH. ALL RIGHT.

33:29.209 --> 33:30.310
OKAY. I GOT IT.

33:30.343 --> 33:32.112
HOW ABOUT THAT TANK, CHALMERS?

33:32.145 --> 33:33.446
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING --
NORRIS FOR CHALMERS.

33:33.480 --> 33:36.116
NORRIS FOR CHALMERS. YEAH.

33:36.149 --> 33:37.584
ALL RIGHT,
CHALMERS FOR PINKELTON

33:37.617 --> 33:39.519
AND A THIRD-ROUND DRAFT CHOICE.

33:39.552 --> 33:41.287
YEAH, LOOK,
I'M TRYING TO HELP YOU HERE.

33:41.321 --> 33:42.589
I MEAN, YOU STARTED WITH A KIWI,

33:42.622 --> 33:44.691
AND I'M GIVING YOU
THREE PAPAYAS.

33:44.724 --> 33:46.593
IT'S A FRUIT ANALOGY.

33:46.626 --> 33:48.228
I CAN PUT TOGETHER
TAYLOR AND CHALMERS

33:48.261 --> 33:50.330
FOR THE FIRST-ROUND PICK.

33:50.363 --> 33:53.400
OKAY, YOU BETTER THINK FAST.
I GOT A LOT OF BALLS IN THE AIR.

33:53.433 --> 33:55.301
TRADE DEADLINE'S
COMING UP QUICK.

33:55.335 --> 33:56.536
OKAY, THANK YOU.

33:56.569 --> 33:58.271
ALL RIGHT.

33:58.304 --> 33:59.606
HEY!
Troy: HEY!

33:59.639 --> 34:01.474
WE GOT EVERY G.M.
IN THE LEAGUE CALLING,

34:01.508 --> 34:03.143
REPORTERS
KNOCKING DOWN THE DOOR.

34:03.176 --> 34:04.611
WHERE ARE WE, PAL?

34:04.644 --> 34:07.480
THIS TERRENCE KING DEAL
HAS A LOT OF MOVING PARTS.

34:07.514 --> 34:10.250
SO, YOU TURNED THE LEAGUE
UPSIDE DOWN

34:10.283 --> 34:12.385
FOR TERRENCE KING?
MM-HMM.

34:12.419 --> 34:13.520
TO SHOW THAT
WE STILL GOT IT.

34:13.553 --> 34:15.622
AND? DO WE?

34:15.655 --> 34:18.258
LAST PIECE OF THE PUZZLE
RIGHT ACROSS THE HUDSON.

34:19.759 --> 34:21.261
NEW JERSEY.

34:21.294 --> 34:23.496
[ LAUGHS ]

34:23.530 --> 34:24.631
WELL,
THAT'S NEVER GONNA HAPPEN.

34:24.664 --> 34:27.267
THE OWNER OF THE BOBCATS
HATES YOU

34:27.300 --> 34:29.302
THANKS TO YOUR WEEKEND GETAWAY
WITH HIS DAUGHTER.

34:29.336 --> 34:31.471
WHO, FOR THE RECORD,
WAS 26.

34:31.504 --> 34:34.207
SURE.
AND WHO LIKES ME SO MUCH

34:34.240 --> 34:35.775
THAT SHE JUST
TOLD HER FATHER

34:35.809 --> 34:38.578
THAT HER FAVORITE FOOTBALL
PLAYER IS MR. TERRENCE KING.

34:38.611 --> 34:40.513
AND HOW MUCH
DID THAT COST YOU?

34:40.547 --> 34:42.215
THREE DAYS IN BELIZE.

34:42.248 --> 34:43.383
MM.

34:43.416 --> 34:44.517
NEW JERSEY'S ON LINE ONE.

34:44.551 --> 34:46.186
BOOM!

34:46.219 --> 34:47.654
WITH TWO HOURS TO SPARE.
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

34:47.687 --> 34:48.655
YES?

34:48.688 --> 34:50.256
HELLO, SIR. YES.

34:50.290 --> 34:51.424
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR TAKING MY CALL.

34:54.594 --> 34:57.263
OH, I THINK
YOU'RE GONNA BE HAPPY.

34:57.297 --> 34:59.666
TWO INITIALS -- T.K.

34:59.699 --> 35:02.469
Dani:
WHAT DOES SHE MEAN TO YOU?

35:02.502 --> 35:04.204
WHAT DOES ANJELICA
MEAN TO ME?

35:04.237 --> 35:06.339
WHAT, IS THIS BOOK GROUP
ALL OF A SUDDEN?

35:06.373 --> 35:08.441
DOESN'T MATTER ANYWAY.
I'M NOT WRITING THE BOOK.

35:08.475 --> 35:10.543
THEY CAN SUE ME,
TORCH ME, WHATEVER.

35:10.577 --> 35:12.278
I'M DONE WITH "RUN."

35:12.312 --> 35:15.615
YOU SAID THAT PUTTING THE BOOK
TO BED WAS LIKE...

35:15.648 --> 35:19.285
SAYING GOODBYE
TO AN OLD FRIEND.

35:19.319 --> 35:21.521
IS ANJELICA
BASED ON A REAL PERSON?

35:23.656 --> 35:25.291
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

35:25.325 --> 35:27.627
I DIDN'T.

35:27.660 --> 35:28.728
IT WAS JUST A HUNCH.

35:33.600 --> 35:35.769
A GIRL I KNEW
IN HIGH SCHOOL, ANGIE --

35:35.802 --> 35:37.704
SHE WAS BEAUTIFUL,

35:37.737 --> 35:40.707
SMART, KIND.

35:40.740 --> 35:42.475
BARELY KNEW I EXISTED.

35:42.509 --> 35:44.310
BUT WE NEVER SPOKE.

35:44.344 --> 35:47.681
NOTHING RISKED,
NOTHING LOST.

35:47.714 --> 35:50.717
SO YOU STARTED
WRITING STORIES,

35:50.750 --> 35:53.553
ESCAPING INTO A WORLD

35:53.586 --> 35:58.291
WHERE...HER REJECTION
WOULDN'T BE A THREAT.

35:58.324 --> 36:01.828
THE PERFECT CURE
FOR A SOCIALLY AWKWARD BOY.

36:01.861 --> 36:04.431
HMM.

36:04.464 --> 36:06.766
YOU SAID THAT NO WOMAN

36:06.800 --> 36:10.337
WOULD BE A MISTRESS
TO ALL THIS.

36:10.370 --> 36:11.871
HAVE THERE BEEN RELATIONSHIPS

36:11.905 --> 36:15.642
THAT HAVE LASTED
ANY PERIOD OF TIME?

36:18.645 --> 36:20.747
OKAY.

36:20.780 --> 36:23.416
NO.

36:23.450 --> 36:26.753
I HAVEN'T HAD VERY MANY
REAL RELATIONSHIPS.

36:26.786 --> 36:29.789
MAYBE I LIKE BEING ALONE.

36:29.823 --> 36:31.558
DO YOU?

36:31.591 --> 36:35.328
WRITING THE FINALE
IS NOT ABOUT

36:35.362 --> 36:40.767
THE HORROR
OF A BLANK PAGE, WILLIAM.

36:40.800 --> 36:43.870
YOU ARE
IN LOVE WITH ANJELICA.

36:43.903 --> 36:45.739
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

36:45.772 --> 36:47.640
LISTEN.

36:47.674 --> 36:50.643
THE -- THE --
THE MING DYNASTY SWORD --

36:50.677 --> 36:53.313
IT PROTECTED ANJELICA

36:53.346 --> 36:54.781
IN "BLOOD VANITY,"
THE THIRD BOOK.

36:54.814 --> 36:57.784
THE COMIC BOOK
THAT YOU TRIED TO BUY --

36:57.817 --> 37:01.321
IT BELONGED TO HER
IN "BRIDGE INTO DEATH."

37:01.354 --> 37:04.324
YOU ARE NOT
OBSESSED WITH SHOPPING.

37:04.357 --> 37:05.859
YOU ARE
OBSESSED WITH ANJELICA.

37:09.429 --> 37:11.798
SHE'S ALL I HAVE.

37:17.704 --> 37:20.640
WILLIAM...

37:20.674 --> 37:22.676
YOU ARE EXHIBITING SIGNS

37:22.709 --> 37:25.345
OF AVOIDANT PERSONALITY
DISORDER.

37:25.378 --> 37:28.948
IT'S WHERE PEOPLE
AVOID INTIMATE RELATIONSHIPS

37:28.982 --> 37:32.419
AT ANY COST
FOR FEAR OF REJECTION.

37:32.452 --> 37:36.690
AND OFTEN
THEY TURN TO FANTASY

37:36.723 --> 37:38.858
TO ESCAPE THEIR REALITY.

37:41.728 --> 37:44.698
YOU JUST DESCRIBED
MY ENTIRE LIFE.

37:44.731 --> 37:49.502
YOUR ENTIRE LIFE...
SO FAR.

37:49.536 --> 37:51.404
YOU AND I
CAN WORK TOGETHER,

37:51.438 --> 37:54.541
AND YOU CAN HAVE
A NORMAL LIFE.

37:54.574 --> 37:59.446
BUT YOU NEED TO FINISH
ANJELICA'S STORY

37:59.479 --> 38:00.914
BEFORE YOU CAN
BEGIN YOUR OWN.

38:04.684 --> 38:05.919
[ SIGHS ]

38:05.952 --> 38:07.587
IT'S FUNNY --
ALL THE DIFFERENT THINGS

38:07.620 --> 38:08.955
THAT PEOPLE FIND SCARY, EH?

38:16.563 --> 38:19.632
SO I GUESS I CAN
CALL OFF THE SEARCH PARTY.

38:19.666 --> 38:21.801
YOU DON'T TEXT.
YOU DON'T DRUNK-DIAL.

38:21.835 --> 38:23.436
I'VE BEEN REALLY BUSY,
OKAY?

38:23.470 --> 38:24.871
I CAN BARELY
KEEP UP WITH THE JOB.

38:24.904 --> 38:27.607
ABOUT THE JOB.

38:27.640 --> 38:29.909
IT SEEMS YOUR ENTHUSIASM
IS WANING A BIT.

38:31.745 --> 38:33.713
[ SIGHS ]

38:33.747 --> 38:36.683
LOOK, I JUST THINK
THAT WORK IS COMPLICATED.

38:36.716 --> 38:39.386
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE WE SHOULD KEEP IT SIMPLE,

38:39.419 --> 38:41.821
LIKE IT WAS BEFORE.

38:41.855 --> 38:43.923
HMM. [ CHUCKLES ]

38:46.559 --> 38:49.496
MAYBE THE FAST TRACK
ISN'T FOR YOU AFTER ALL.

38:58.938 --> 39:01.508
Dani:
WHAT IS ALL OF THIS?

39:01.541 --> 39:03.410
IT LOOKS LIKE
A LIST OF CONTRIBUTIONS

39:03.443 --> 39:05.845
V3 FOUNDATION
MADE TO CHARITIES LAST YEAR.

39:05.879 --> 39:08.515
WELL, CARL WAS
IN CHARGE OF ALL OF THAT.

39:08.548 --> 39:09.683
WHOA.

39:09.716 --> 39:12.018
LOOKS LIKE V3 MADE

39:12.052 --> 39:14.487
SOME PRETTY GENEROUS
DONATIONS.

39:14.521 --> 39:17.057
CARL SAID THERE WERE
EIGHT CHARITIES

39:17.090 --> 39:19.592
V3 DONATED TO.
MM-HMM.

39:19.626 --> 39:21.461
THIS LISTS NINE.

39:21.494 --> 39:24.731
THE NINTH BEING THIS
CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL.

39:24.764 --> 39:25.999
GRAND CAYMAN.

39:26.032 --> 39:28.868
CAYMAN ISLANDS.

39:28.902 --> 39:29.936
[ GROANS ]

39:29.969 --> 39:32.005
WELL, I'M NO EXPERT,

39:32.038 --> 39:34.641
BUT ISN'T THAT
WHERE PEOPLE LAUNDER MONEY?

39:34.674 --> 39:37.877
CARL WASN'T
STEALING MONEY FROM V3.

39:37.911 --> 39:40.647
HE WAS MOVING IT.

39:40.680 --> 39:42.949
THE QUESTION NOW IS FOR WHO?
AND WHY?

39:53.560 --> 39:55.895
[ GASPS ] AH.

39:55.929 --> 39:57.163
[ SIGHS ]

39:57.197 --> 39:59.432
YOU REALLY
KNOW HOW TO MAKE AN ENTRANCE.

40:01.167 --> 40:03.036
MAYBE AN EXIT.

40:03.069 --> 40:04.871
MEANING?

40:04.904 --> 40:08.608
MEANING I JUST CAME
TO SAY GOODBYE AND THANK YOU.

40:08.641 --> 40:11.077
FOR WHAT?

40:11.111 --> 40:14.147
YOU KNOW, YOU NEVER
GIVE UP ON YOUR CLIENTS,

40:14.180 --> 40:16.116
AND YOU HAVEN'T
GIVEN UP ON ME,

40:16.149 --> 40:18.818
EVEN THOUGH I'M GONE.

40:18.852 --> 40:21.988
BUT THAT DOESN'T
STOP ME FROM FEELING GUILTY.

40:22.022 --> 40:24.557
NO.

40:24.591 --> 40:26.593
I'M THE ONE
WITH THE GUILT.

40:26.626 --> 40:28.161
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:28.194 --> 40:30.897
I DID SOME BAD THINGS.

40:30.930 --> 40:32.999
MAKE IT RIGHT, DOC.

40:33.033 --> 40:34.834
FINISH WHAT I STARTED.

40:34.868 --> 40:37.203
CARL, I'M TRYING.

40:37.237 --> 40:41.074
I'M REALLY TRYING.

40:43.543 --> 40:46.079
CARL?

40:46.112 --> 40:48.281
CARL?

40:48.314 --> 40:52.285
* THERE'S A GHOST IN MY HOUSE

40:52.318 --> 40:56.589
* BUT NOBODY BELIEVES ME
[ GROANS ]

40:56.623 --> 41:01.061
* THERE'S A SPIRIT IN THE DARK

41:01.094 --> 41:04.597
* THAT ONLY I CAN SEE

41:06.232 --> 41:08.268
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S WORSE --

41:08.301 --> 41:09.969
GETTING MY FOOTBALL HEART
RIPPED OUT

41:10.003 --> 41:11.638
OR RIPPING OUT
MY<i>HEART</i>HEART.

41:11.871 --> 41:14.274
WELL, CAN'T HELP YOU
IN THE ROMANCE DEPARTMENT,

41:14.307 --> 41:16.943
BUT I MIGHT BE ABLE

41:16.976 --> 41:18.945
E
BACK INTO YOU.

41:20.647 --> 41:22.949
HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT NEW JERSEY
THIS TIME OF YEAR?

41:22.982 --> 41:25.251
JERSEY? SERIOUSLY?

41:27.320 --> 41:29.956
ISN'T THAT WITH COACH --
Purnell: HELLO, TERRENCE.

41:29.989 --> 41:31.558
PURNELL?

41:31.591 --> 41:33.526
YOU READY TO PLAY
SOME FOOTBALL?

41:36.696 --> 41:38.965
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

41:38.998 --> 41:40.567
[ LAUGHS ]

41:40.600 --> 41:42.335
HELL YEAH!

41:42.369 --> 41:44.104
WELCOME TO THE BOBCATS.

41:44.137 --> 41:46.039
WE'RE GONNA KICK
WIZNEWSKI'S NAPOLEONIC ASS

41:46.072 --> 41:47.273
BACK TO THE ISLE OF ELBA.

41:47.307 --> 41:49.242
[ LAUGHS ]

41:51.344 --> 41:53.346
HEY.

41:53.380 --> 41:55.248
I HEAR YOU KICKED
THE WRITER'S BLOCK
RIGHT OUT OF GLASS.

41:55.281 --> 42:05.625
NICE WORK.

42:10.997 --> 42:12.265
YOU OKAY, SANTINO?

42:12.298 --> 42:14.134
I'M JUST HAVING TROUBLE

42:14.167 --> 42:16.603
SHAKING
THE GHOST OF CARL.

42:19.205 --> 42:20.707
WELL, WE'RE ALL
HAUNTED BY WHAT HAPPENED,

42:20.740 --> 42:22.142
BUT WE GOT TO
KEEP MOVING FORWARD.

42:22.175 --> 42:24.044
CARL'S STORY'S OVER.

42:24.077 --> 42:25.011
WE'RE ALL STILL HERE.

42:25.045 --> 42:27.047
RIGHT.

42:27.080 --> 42:29.616
LIFE SURE IS
A PAGE-TURNER, ISN'T IT?

42:29.649 --> 42:31.918
YES.

42:31.951 --> 42:35.288
AND I CAN'T WAIT TO SEE
WHAT HAPPENS NEXT.

42:35.321 --> 42:36.990
THAT'S THE FUN OF IT.

42:42.062 --> 42:43.329
CARRY ON.
[ CHUCKLES ]
